<subSubSection box="[199,986,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,290,1145]" box="[199,986,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a reference to the unusually short arista.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,290,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1088,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">Remarks.</emphasis>
In Emden’s (1951) key the new species runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Emden" authorityName="Emden" authorityYear="1951" box="[816,1099,1087,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Spilogona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscotriangulata">
<emphasis box="[816,1018,1087,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="296">S. fuscotriangulata</emphasis>
Emden
</taxonomicName>
at couplet 27, but differs by the unspotted abdomen.
</paragraph>
